  66:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  67:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                       ##### Simple mode v.s. waveform mode #####
  68:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  69:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****   [..] The HRTIM HAL API is split into 2 categories:
  70:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Simple functions: these functions allow for using a HRTIM timer as a
  71:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        general purpose timer with high resolution capabilities.
  72:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        HRTIM simple modes are managed through the set of functions named
  73:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        HAL_HRTIM_Simple<Function>. These functions are similar in name and usage
  74:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        to the one defined for the TIM peripheral. When a HRTIM timer operates in
  75:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        simple mode, only a very limited set of HRTIM features are used.
  76:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        Following simple modes are proposed:
  77:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)Output compare mode,
  78:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)PWM output mode,
  79:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)Input capture mode,
  80:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          (++)One pulse mode.
  81:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Waveform functions: These functions allow taking advantage of the HRTIM
  82:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        flexibility to produce numerous types of control signal. When a HRTIM timer
  83:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        operates in waveform mode, all the HRTIM features are accessible without
  84:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        any restriction. HRTIM waveform modes are managed through the set of
  85:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        functions named HAL_HRTIM_Waveform<Function>
  86:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
  87:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                       ##### How to use this driver #####
ARM GAS  C:\msys64\tmp\cceOZfWE.s 			page 3


  88:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** ==============================================================================
  89:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     [..]
  90:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#)Initialize the HRTIM low level resources by implementing the
  91:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         HAL_HRTIM_MspInit() function:
  92:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Enable the HRTIM clock source using __HRTIMx_CLK_ENABLE()
  93:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Connect HRTIM pins to MCU I/Os
  94:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++) Enable the clock for the HRTIM GPIOs using the following
  95:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   function: __HAL_RCC_GPIOx_CLK_ENABLE()
  96:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++) Configure these GPIO pins in Alternate Function mode using
  97:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   HAL_GPIO_Init()
  98:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)When using DMA to control data transfer (e.g HAL_HRTIM_SimpleBaseStart_DMA())
  99:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Enable the DMAx interface clock using __DMAx_CLK_ENABLE()
 100:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Initialize the DMA handle
 101:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Associate the initialized DMA handle to the appropriate DMA
 102:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  handle of the HRTIM handle using __HAL_LINKDMA()
 103:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Initialize the DMA channel using HAL_DMA_Init()
 104:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the transfer
 105:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  complete interrupt on the DMA channel using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority()
 106:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
 107:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)In case of using interrupt mode (e.g HAL_HRTIM_SimpleBaseStart_IT())
 108:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****             (+++)Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the concerned
 109:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                  HRTIM interrupt using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
 110:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 111:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Initialize the HRTIM HAL using HAL_HRTIM_Init(). The HRTIM configuration
 112:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        structure (field of the HRTIM handle) specifies which global interrupt of
 113:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        whole HRTIM must be enabled (Burst mode period, System fault, Faults).
 114:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        It also contains the HRTIM external synchronization configuration. HRTIM
 115:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        can act as a master (generating a synchronization signal) or as a slave
 116:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        (waiting for a trigger to be synchronized).
 117:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 118:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)Start the high resolution unit using HAL_HRTIM_DLLCalibrationStart(). DLL
 119:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        calibration is executed periodically and compensate for potential voltage
 120:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        and temperature drifts. DLL calibration period is specified by the
 121:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        CalibrationRate argument.
 122:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 123:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****     (#)HRTIM timers cannot be used until the high resolution unit is ready. This
 124:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        can be checked using HAL_HRTIM_PollForDLLCalibration(): this function returns
 125:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        HAL_OK if DLL calibration is completed or HAL_TIMEOUT if the DLL calibration
 126:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        is still going on when timeout given as argument expires. DLL calibration
 127:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        can also be started in interrupt mode using HAL_HRTIM_DLLCalibrationStart_IT().
 128:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        In that case an interrupt is generated when the DLL calibration is completed.
 129:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        Note that as DLL calibration is executed on a periodic basis an interrupt
 130:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****        will be generated at the end of every DLL calibration operation
 131:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****       (worst case: one interrupt every 14 micro seconds !).
 132:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 133:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Configure HRTIM resources shared by all HRTIM timers
 134:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Burst Mode Controller:
 135:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_BurstModeConfig(): configures the HRTIM burst mode
 136:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      controller: operating mode (continuous or one-shot mode), clock
 137:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      (source, prescaler) , trigger(s), period, idle duration.
 138:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)External Events Conditioning:
 139:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_EventConfig(): configures the conditioning of an
 140:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      external event channel: source, polarity, edge-sensitivity.
 141:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      External event can be used as triggers (timer reset, input
 142:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      capture, burst mode, ADC triggers, delayed protection)
 143:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      They can also be used to set or reset timer outputs. Up to
 144:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      10 event channels are available.
ARM GAS  C:\msys64\tmp\cceOZfWE.s 			page 4


 145:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_EventPrescalerConfig(): configures the external
 146:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      event sampling clock (used for digital filtering).
 147:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)Fault Conditioning:
 148:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultConfig(): configures the conditioning of a
 149:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      fault channel: source, polarity, edge-sensitivity. Fault
 150:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      channels are used to disable the outputs in case of an
 151:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      abnormal operation. Up to 5 fault channels are available.
 152:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultPrescalerConfig(): configures the fault
 153:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      sampling clock (used for digital filtering).
 154:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_FaultModeCtl(): Enables or disables fault input(s)
 155:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      circuitry. By default all fault inputs are disabled.
 156:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****         (##)ADC trigger:
 157:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)HAL_HRTIM_ADCTriggerConfig(): configures the source triggering
 158:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      the update of the ADC trigger register and the ADC trigger.
 159:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      4 independent triggers are available to start both the regular
 160:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      and the injected sequencers of the 2 ADCs
 161:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 162:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Configure HRTIM timer time base using HAL_HRTIM_TimeBaseConfig(). This
 163:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****          function must be called whatever the HRTIM timer operating mode is
