 195:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 196:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Completes waveform timer configuration
 197:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformTimerConfig(): configuration of a HRTIM timer
 198:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   operating in wave form mode mainly consists in:
 199:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the HRTIM timer interrupts and DMA requests.
 200:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the half mode for the HRTIM timer.
 201:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Defining how the HRTIM timer reacts to external synchronization input.
ARM GAS  C:\msys64\tmp\cceOZfWE.s 			page 5


 202:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the push-pull mode for the HRTIM timer.
 203:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the fault channels for the HRTIM timer.
 204:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Enabling the dead-time insertion for the HRTIM timer.
 205:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Setting the delayed protection mode for the HRTIM timer (source and outputs
 206:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                      on which the delayed protection are applied).
 207:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Specifying the HRTIM timer update and reset triggers.
 208:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Specifying the HRTIM timer registers update policy (e.g. pre-load enabling).
 209:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_TimerEventFilteringConfig(): configures external
 210:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   event blanking and windowing circuitry of a HRTIM timer:
 211:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Blanking:  to mask external events during a defined  time period a defined tim
 212:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Windowing, to enable external events only during a defined time period
 213:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_DeadTimeConfig(): configures the dead-time insertion
 214:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   unit for a HRTIM timer. Allows to generate a couple of
 215:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   complementary signals from a single reference waveform,
 216:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   with programmable delays between active state.
 217:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_ChopperModeConfig(): configures the parameters of
 218:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   the high-frequency carrier signal added on top of the timing
 219:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   unit output. Chopper mode can be enabled or disabled for each
 220:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                    timer output separately (see  HAL_HRTIM_WaveformOutputConfig()).
 221:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_BurstDMAConfig(): configures the burst DMA burst
 222:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   controller. Allows having multiple HRTIM registers updated
 223:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   with a single DMA request. The burst DMA operation is started
 224:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   by calling HAL_HRTIM_BurstDMATransfer().
 225:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformCompareConfig():configures the compare unit
 226:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   of a HRTIM timer. This operation consists in setting the
 227:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   compare value and possibly specifying the auto delayed mode
 228:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   for compare units 2 and 4 (allows to have compare events
 229:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   generated relatively to capture events). Note that when auto
 230:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   delayed mode is needed, the capture unit associated to the
 231:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   compare unit must be configured separately.
 232:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformCaptureConfig(): configures the capture unit
 233:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   of a HRTIM timer. This operation consists in specifying the
 234:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   source(s)  triggering the capture (timer register update event,
 235:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   external event, timer output set/reset event, other HRTIM
 236:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   timer related events).
 237:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformOutputConfig(): configuration of a HRTIM timer
 238:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   output mainly consists in:
 239:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Setting the output polarity (active high or active low),
 240:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Defining the set/reset crossbar for the output,
 241:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                 (+++)Specifying the fault level (active or inactive) in IDLE and FAULT states.,
 242:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 243:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (#) Set waveform timer output(s) level
 244:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****               (++)HAL_HRTIM_WaveformSetOutputLevel(): forces the output to its
 245:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****                   active or inactive level. For example, when deadtime insertion
