 338:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 339:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 340:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Both functions take as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 341:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 342:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 343:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 344:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Use function HAL_HRTIM_UnRegisterCallback or HAL_HRTIM_TIMxUnRegisterCallback
 345:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      to reset a callback to the default weak function. Both functions take  as parameters
 346:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 347:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 348:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 349:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      By default, after the HAL_HRTIM_Init() and when the state is HAL_HRTIM_STATE_RESET
 350:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions (e.g HAL_HRTIM_Fault1Callback)
 351:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are reset to the legacy
 352:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      weak functions in the HAL_HRTIM_Init()/ HAL_HRTIM_DeInit() only when these
 353:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      callbacks are null (not registered beforehand). If MspInit or MspDeInit are
 354:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      not null, the HAL_HRTIM_Init()/ HAL_HRTIM_DeInit() keep and use the user
 355:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 356:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 357:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 358:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_HRTIM_STATE_READY state only.
 359:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 360:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      in HAL_HRTIM_STATE_READY or HAL_HRTIM_STATE_RESET states, thus registered
 361:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 362:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 363:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      using HAL_HRTIM_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_HRTIM_DeInit()
 364:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      or HAL_HRTIM_Init() function.
 365:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 366:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      [..]
 367:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      When the compilation flag USE_HAL_HRTIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 368:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all
 369:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****      callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 370:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c **** 
 371:Drivers/STM32F3xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f3xx_hal_hrtim.c ****   @endverbatim
